      <div class="container">
        <h1 class="mt-5" id="abhi2">Theory:- </h1>
        <p class="lead">The process of deriving a string is called as derivation. The geometrical representation of a derivation is called as a parse tree or derivation tree.</p>
        <p class="lead">Properties Of Parse Tree-</p>
        <ul class="lead">
          <li>
              <p class="lead">Root node of a parse tree is the start symbol of the grammar.</p>
          </li>
          <li>
              <p class="lead">Each leaf node of a parse tree represents a terminal symbol.</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p class="lead">â€¢	Each interior node of a parse tree represents a non-terminal symbol.</p>
        </li>
      </ul>
      <br><br>
